Criteria, Ferrovial, Galp Energia: Iberian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-04-29T04:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/criteria-ferrovial-galp-energia-iberian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  added 1.2 percent to 10,867.8.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  gained 0.4 percent to 7,647.63.  Spanish stocks:  Criteria CaixaCorp SA (CRI)  : The investment unit of
Spain’s largest savings bank will report first-quarter earnings.
The shares added 0.7 percent to 5.06 euros.  Ferrovial SA (FER)  : The Spanish builder and
infrastructure company reported a profit of 224 million euros
($331.4 million) in the first quarter. The shares slipped 0.2
percent to 9.38 euros.  Solaria Energia y Medio Ambiente SA (SLR)  : The solar
energy company said it bought back 54,510 shares from April 15
through April 26 at 2.10 euros to 2.20 euros each. The shares
added 2.1 percent to 2.24 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Galp Energia SGPS SA (GALP)  : Portugal’s biggest oil
company is scheduled to report first-quarter earnings before the
start of trading. The stock fell 0.1 percent to 14.58.  -- Editor: Joanna Ossinger  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net  or  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
